      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(video-task): add delivering status to break self-deadlock in scheduleMediaGenerationTaskCompletion",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\n\\`video_generate\\` background tasks stay in \\`running\\` status for several minutes **after** the generated video is ready, blocking the next segment in sequential video-production workflows. The self-deadlock chain:\n\n1. \\`scheduleMediaGenerationTaskCompletion\\` generates video → task is still \\`running\\`\n2. \\`wakeTaskCompletion\\` with \\`expectFinal: true\\` awaits the requester agent's full turn\n3. The woken agent tries to start the next video segment → but finds an active \\`running\\` task\n4. The prompt-context guard injects a retry-suppression warning → agent yields\n5. Task only flips to \\`succeeded\\` after the agent gives up → 4-5 min \"release tax\" per segment\n\n## Solution\n\nIntroduce a **\\`delivering\\`** intermediate status between \"generated\" and \"terminal\". After media generation completes, the task transitions from \\`running\\` to \\`delivering\\` before delivery confirmation begins. The duplicate-guard and active-task prompt helpers treat \\`delivering\\` as non-blocking for distinct requests, so the agent can start the next segment while delivery confirmation is still pending.\n\n### Key changes\n\n- **task-registry.types.ts**: Added \\`\"delivering\"\\` to \\`TaskStatus\\` union and \\`TASK_STATUSES\\` set\n- **task-registry.ts**: Exported \\`markTaskDeliveringByRunId\\` to transition tasks from \\`running\\` to \\`delivering\\`\n- **media-generate-background-shared.ts**: Call \\`markTaskDeliveringByRunId\\` after \\`withMediaGenerationTaskKeepalive\\` returns (media ready), before \\`wakeTaskCompletion\\`\n- **media-generation-task-status-shared.ts**: \\`listActiveMediaGenerationTasksForSession\\` excludes \\`delivering\\` tasks; status text shows appropriate delivery-phase message\n- **All active-task checks** (task-registry, executor, flow-registry, audit, summary, acp-spawn, session-async-task-status): Recognize \\`delivering\\` as non-terminal active status\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Test matrix\n\n| Test file | Tests | Result |\n|-----------|-------|--------|\n| \\`media-generate-background-shared.test.ts\\` | 17 | ✅ Passed |\n| \\`video-generation-task-status.test.ts\\` | 8 | ✅ Passed |\n| \\`video-generate-tool.status.test.ts\\` | 6 | ✅ Passed |\n| \\`task-registry.test.ts\\` | 108 | ✅ Passed |\n| \\`task-executor.test.ts\\` | (108 total above) | ✅ |\n| \\`task-flow-registry.test.ts\\` | (108 total above) | ✅ |\n| \\`task-status.test.ts\\` | (included in media shard) | ✅ |\n\n**Total**: 131 tests passed across all affected modules.\n\n### Formatting check\n\\`oxfmt --check\\`: ✅ Passed (12 files)\n\n### Diff summary\n\\`\\`\\`\n12 files changed, 69 insertions(+), 14 deletions(-)\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n## Safety\n\n- Preserves the existing completion-delivery safety contract: \\`completeTaskRun\\` still runs after delivery confirmation\n- The \\`delivering\\` status is non-terminal, so task audits and flow tracking correctly treat it as active\n- Same-request duplicate guard (\\`isTaskStillBlockingDuplicateGuard\\`) is unchanged; \\`delivering\\` tasks still block **identical** duplicate requests\n- Only \\`listActiveMediaGenerationTasksForSession\\` (used for prompt-context warnings) excludes \\`delivering\\` tasks, allowing distinct follow-up requests to proceed\n",
        "branch": "fix/issue-95701-video-task-deadlock",
